But those who accept the testimony of the manuscripts are at least entitled to ask whether the evidence which has accumulated in favour of the authorship of Tacitus does not outweigh the counter- arguments which must force those who adopt them into assuming the existence of some unknown writer, who otherwise makes no appearance in the literature of his own day. .
